from datetime import datetime

# Define the date
date_str = "10/19/2022"

# Convert the string to a datetime object
date_obj = datetime.strptime(date_str, "%m/%d/%Y")

# Get the day of the week
day_of_week = date_obj.strftime("%A")
day_of_week
